def: A grandmother; a grandam; familiarly, an old woman. Granny'sbend, or Granny's knot (Naut.), a kind of insecure knot or hitch; areef knot crossed the wrong way.
The act of deifying; exaltation to divine honors; apotheosis;excessive praise.
A cruciferous herb of certain species of Dentaria; -- calledalso toothwort, tooth violet, or pepper root.
The quality of being courtly; elegance or dignity of manners.
A universal remedy; -- name formerly to a purgative electuary.
A binary compound of carbon with some other element or radical,in which the carbon plays the part of a negative; -- formerly termedcarburet.
To break completely; to break in pieces. [Obs.]With nose and mouth to-broke. Chaucer.
In an equal manner or degree in equal shares or proportion;with equal and impartial justice; without difference; alike; evenly;justly; as, equally taxed, furnished, etc.
